Meghan Markle | Photo – Good Morning America Meghan Markle’s former Suits co-star has shared several throwback photos of the Duchess to celebrate a day that is very special to her. This week will mark her last episode in the film “Suits” Patrick Adams, who plays Meghan’s character Rachel Zane’s husband Mike Ross in the hit legal drama, shared behind-the-scenes snap to mark the final episode of the show.   A post shared by Patrick Adams (@halfadams) on Sep 22, 2019 at 10:31pm PDT  They include a photo of the Duchess in a white fluffy dressing gown, one of her standing outside of her dressing room and a snap of her lying on the floor with her legs on a cupboard.   A post shared by Patrick Adams (@halfadams) on Sep 22, 2019 at 10:38pm PDT  Sharing a photo of himself at a costume fitting from series one, he wrote: “This week the last episode of Suits will air and the nearly 10 year journey we’ve all been on together will finally be over..  “So it seems right to post some photos the next couple of days from the early days. This photo was from the first fitting I ever had for Mike Ross.   This week the last episode of Suits will air and the nearly 10 year journey we’ve all been on together will finally be over. So it seems right to post some photos the next couple of days from the early days. This photo was from the first fitting I ever had for Mike Ross. A post shared by  Patrick Adams (@halfadams) on Sep 22, 2019 at 10:14pm PDT  Meghan starred in the TV show for seven years, and fans were heartbroken when she decided to quit to dedicate herself to her royal duties after her relationship with Harry became official. 